README.md

Build Status

   A curated list of awesome Fortran frameworks, libraries and software.
   Inspired by [https://github.com/Wolg/awesome-swift]awesome-swift by
   @Wolg.
     * Awesome Fortran
          + Functional Libraries
          + Graphics Libraries
          + Math libs
          + JSON Manipulation
          + XML Manipulation
          + Date and time manipulation
          + Testing
          + Encoding-Decoding
          + Portability enabling
          + Command-Line parsing
          + Compiling and building
          + Preprocessor
          + Automatic documentation
          + Computational Fluid
            Dynamics
          + [file://localhost/Users/admin/Pros/sh/awesome/awe_raw/awesome-
            fortran#docker]Docker
     * [file://localhost/Users/admin/Pros/sh/awesome/awe_raw/awesome-fortr
       an#resources]Resources
          + [file://localhost/Users/admin/Pros/sh/awesome/awe_raw/awesome-
            fortran#fortran-websites]Fortran Websites
               o [file://localhost/Users/admin/Pros/sh/awesome/awe_raw/awe
                 some-fortran#fortran-videos]Fortran Videos
     * [file://localhost/Users/admin/Pros/sh/awesome/awe_raw/awesome-fortr
       an#other-awesome-lists]Other Awesome Lists
     * [file://localhost/Users/admin/Pros/sh/awesome/awe_raw/awesome-fortr
       an#contributing]Contributing

Functional Libraries

     * [https://github.com/wavebitscientific/functional-fortran]Functional
       Frotran - Functional programming for modern Fortran.

Graphics Libraries

   Libraries for graphing, graphics, and GUIs
     * [http://www.mps.mpg.de/dislin/]DISLIN - a high-level graphing and
       user-interface library.
     * [http://math.nist.gov/f90gl/]f90gl - public domain implementation
       of the official NIST Fortran 90 bindings for OpenGL.
     * [http://www-stone.ch.cam.ac.uk/pub/f03gl/index.xhtml]F03GL - a
       Fortran 2003 interface to the OpenGL library, along with the GLU
       and GLUT toolkits.
     * [https://github.com/jerryd/gtk-fortran/wiki]gtk-fortran - a
       cross-platform library to build Graphical User Interfaces (GUI)
       using [https://www.gtk.org/]GTK+. Very useful when combined with
       the [https://glade.gnome.org/]Glade RAD tool.
     * [http://www.astro.caltech.edu/%7Etjp/pgplot/]PGPLOT -
       cross-platform scientific graphing library.
     * [https://github.com/szaghi/VTKFortran]VTKFortran - Pure Fortran
       (2003+) library to write and read data conforming the VTK standard.

Math Libs

   Libraries for calculating and other mathematical operations.
     * [http://www.netlib.org/blas/]BLAS - application programming
       interface standard for publishing libraries to perform basic linear
       algebra operations such as vector and matrix multiplication.
     * [http://cernlib.web.cern.ch/cernlib/]CERNLIB - The CERN Program
       Library is a large collection of general purpose libraries and
       modules maintained and offered in both source and object code form
       on the CERN central computers
     * [http://www.netlib.org/eispack/]EISPACK - a software library for
       numerical computation of eigenvalues and eigenvectors of matrices,
       written in FORTRAN
     * [http://www.lrz.de/services/software/mathematik/gsl/fortran/index.h
       tml]FGSL - portable, object-based Fortran interface to the
       [http://www.lrz.de/services/software/mathematik/gsl/]GNU scientific
       library
     * [http://www.roguewave.com/products-services/imsl-numerical-librarie
       s/fortran-libraries]IMSL - The IMSL Fortran Numerical Library is
       the standard for high performance computing commercial mathematics
       and statistics libraries
     * [http://www.ssisc.org/lis/index.en.html#download]Lis - a Library of
       Iterative Solvers for Linear Systems
     * [http://www.nag.co.uk/nag-fortran-library]NAG Fortran Library -
       Produced by experts for use in a variety of applications, the NAG
       Fortran Library has a global reputation for its excellence and,
       with hundreds of fully documented and tested routines, is the
       largest collection of mathematical and statistical algorithms
       available
     * [https://github.com/Unidata/netcdf-fortran]netCDF - a set of
       software libraries and self-describing, machine-independent data
       formats that support the creation, access, and sharing of
       array-oriented scientific data.
     * [https://github.com/xianyi/OpenBLAS]OpenBLAS - one of the fastest
       open source BLAS libraries available. Almost as fast as Intel MKL.
     * [http://paw.web.cern.ch/paw/]PAW - conceived as an instrument to
       assist physicists in the analysis and presentation of their data

JSON Manipulation

   Libraries for JSON data manipulating with Fortran language.
     * [https://github.com/josephalevin/fson]FSON - Fortran 95 JSON
       Parser.
     * [https://github.com/jacobwilliams/json-fortran]json-fortran - A
       Fortran 2008 JSON API.

XML Manipulation

   Libraries for XML data manipulating with Fortran language.
     * [https://github.com/andreww/fox]fox - Fortran XML library
     * [https://sourceforge.net/projects/xml-fortran/]xml-fortran - an
       all-Fortran solution for reading and writing XML files.

Date and time manipulation

   Libraries for date and time manipulation with Fortran language.
     * [https://github.com/wavebitscientific/datetime-fortran]datetime-for
       tran - A Fortran 2003 date and time manipulation library, modeled
       after Python's datetime library.

Testing

   Libraries for testing codebases and generating test data.
     * [https://sourceforge.net/projects/fortranxunit/]FRUIT - FORTRAN
       Unit Test Framework, written in FORTRAN 95
     * [http://flibs.sourceforge.net/ftnunit.html]Ftunit - Fortran unit
       testing framework by Arjen Markus
     * [https://sourceforge.net/projects/pfunit/]pFUnit - Unit testing
       framework for Fortran with MPI extensions by developers from NASA
       and NGC TASC. Uses parallel codes and object-oriented design.

Encoding-Decoding

   Libraries for encoding and decoding data with Fortran language.
     * [https://github.com/szaghi/BeFoR64]BeFoR64 - Base64
       encoding/decoding library for FoRtran poor men. A KISS library for
       base64 encoding/decoding for modern (2003+) Fortran projects.

Portability enabling

   Libraries for enabling codes portability.
     * [https://github.com/szaghi/PENF]PENF - Pure Fortran (2003+) library
       for ensuring codes portability.

Command-Line parsing

   Libraries for parsing command-line and building user interfaces.
     * [https://github.com/szaghi/FLAP]FLAP - Fortran command Line
       Arguments Parser for poor men. A KISS library for building easily
       nice Command Line Interfaces (CLI) for modern (2003+) Fortran
       projects.
     * [https://github.com/cngilbreth/optionsf90]options.f90 - Options &
       input processing for modern Fortran.

Compiling and building

   Libraries for compiling and building Fortran projects.
     * [https://github.com/szaghi/FoBiS]FoBiS - Fortran Building System
       for poor men. A KISS tool for automatic building modern Fortran
       projects.

Preprocessor

   Libraries for conditional-compilation, macros for code simplification,
   and inclusion of additional source files, templating systems.
     * [http://blockit.sourceforge.net/]Blockit/PyF95++ - A fairly simple
       Python framework used to block parse your code (or any text file)
       into nested blocks. The BlockIt framework has already been used to
       create a templating capability for the Fortran 95/2003 language
       along with some language extensions.
     * [https://github.com/szaghi/PreForM]PreForM - Preprocessor for
       Fortran poor Men.

Automatic documentation

   Libraries for building documentation.
     * [https://github.com/cmacmackin/ford]FORD - An automatic
       documentation generator for modern Fortran programs.

Computational Fluid Dynamics

   Libraries for CFD computations
     * [https://github.com/szaghi/OFF/tree/testing]OFF - Open source
       Finite volume Fluid dynamics code.

Docker

     * [https://hub.docker.com/r/baekjoon/onlinejudge-fortran/]Unoficial
       Image - docker image provided by @baekjoon

Resources

   Various resources, such as books, websites and articles, for improving
   your Fortran development skills and knowledge.

Fortran Websites

     * [http://www.fortran.com/]The Fortran Company - A home page of
       FORTRAN programming language.
     * [https://fortrandev.wordpress.com/]Fortran Dev - Fortran
       development blog.
     * [http://fortranwiki.org/fortran/show/HomePage]Fortran WIKI - An
       open venue for discussing all aspects of the Fortran programming
       language and scientific computing.

Fortran Videos

     * [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qUy8M10uZRU]GNU FORTRAN Lesson 1 -
       Videos about the Fortran programming language.

Other Awesome Lists

   Other amazingly awesome lists can be found in the
   [https://github.com/bayandin/awesome-awesomeness]awesome-awesomeness
   list.

Contributing

   Your contributions are always welcome! Please submit a pull request or
   create an issue to add a new framework, library or software to the
   list. Do not submit a project, which hasn't been updated in the past 6
   months or is not awesome.

